Spigelian hernia. Diagnosis and surgical treatment. Spigelian hernia (SH) is a rare partial abdominal wall defect its manifestation is rare. Seven cases were observed--4 females and 3 males with mean age of 56.5 years (range 38-65)--in 857 patients operated for hernia (0.8%) between 1995 and 2003. Ultrasound examination avoid the diagnosis and marked the fascial defect, measuring diameter and sac contents. In all cases a surgical approach with an epicritic incision has be done and the fascia defect closed with properitoneal and subfascial polypropylene mesh (Prolene Hernia System, PHS). All patients underwent to follow-up demonstrating no recurrences or complications like mesh suppuration or dislocation.